The tearing apart of limbs from ones body

Specifically used when talking about Dionysus and his cousin Pentheus. Pentheus was lured into the forest by the god after he banned worship of Dionysus. He is attacked by Maenads, followers of Dionysus, as well as by his own mother. The reference of his mother tearing apart his limbs is sparagmos.